nesses this segment provides and manages reward products for loyalty programs the global customer engagement segment creates and manages programs and solutions comprising revenue enhancement and engagement solutions that address companies in the financial institution telecommunications retail and travel sectors the insurance solutions segment offers various insurance solutions consisting of accidental death and serious injury hospital accident plan recuperative care and lump sum life insurance services this segment markets its insurance products primarily through direct mail and the internet the legacy membership and package segment services and supports membership and package programs worldwide as of december   it had approximately  clients operating in various industries including financial services retail travel telecommunications utilities and internet approximately  million subscribers and endcustomers enrolled in customer engagement and insurance programs and approximately  million customers who received loyalty pointsbased management and redemption services or credit or debit card enhancement services the company is headquartered in stamford connecticut affinion group inc is a subsidiary of affinion group holdings inc detailed description  high ridge parkstamford ct united states employees phone  wwwaffinioncom key executives for affinion group inc mr todd h siegel esq chief executive officer and director age  mr michele conforti president and managing director of global customer engagement age  mr gregory s miller chief financial officer and executive vice president age  mr robert lyons chief operating officer and executive vice president age  mr scott lazear president of connexions loyalty age  compensation as of fiscal year  affinion group inc key developments affinion group holdings inc and affinion group inc enter into new senior secured credit facility may   on may   affinion group entered into a new senior secured credit facility the new credit facilit